Chairman of the House of Representatives Committee on Appropriations Hon Muktar Aliyu Betara has been elected unopposed as the candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), for Biu, Bayo, Kwaya/Kusar and Shani Federal Constituency of Borno State. His constituents contributed over N120 million for his nomination form to ensure his emergence as the sole candidate of the APC for a fifth term in the Green Chamber. There was a massive turnout of supporters who came to witness the election, which took place in the four local government areas that makes up the constituency. The primary featured a massive turnout of supporters who came to witness the formality of their illustrious son picking the ticket for the first without any challenger.   2023: Tension in Nasarawa APC over delegates’ list     Aminu Tambuwal’s date with destiny     Opeifa says party supreme over Lagos West APC senatorial…   Betara polled 194 vote out of the 204 accredited delegates across the four local government areas with supporters chanting “Say Betara”, “Say Betara.” In his acceptance speech, the lawmaker thanked his constituents for the show of love. He said: “I am happy my people want me back because i am always on ground for them. This has shown how much they appreciate my effort and i will keep doing more for them. “I want to use this medium to thank everyone for believing in me”, together we will work to achieve goals for the good of our constituents.”